                                  Server creation

1.  instal package.json  (npm init) 
2.  Create node modules - install express - npm i express 
3.  create index.js - main entry point
4.  in index.js
        a.  import express 
        b.  create an app using express 
        c.  setup a port number for communication
        d.  use json parser for server responses 
5.  Integration
        a.  install cors
        b.  import cors into index.js
        c.  using cors describe the origin to the server
                origin: 'http://localhost:4200'
6.  service - Create a folder service
        a.  Create dataservices.js and db.js
7.  Backend and mongodb action
        a.  install mongoose - npm i mongoose
        b.  import mongoose into db.js
        c.  Define the connection string
                mongodb://localhost:27017/cart
        d.  create model for collection(product) and export it
8.  Resolving API calls in index.js
        a.  import dataservises to  index
9.    Create logic in dataservices
        a.   import db
        b.   get all products from db
10. Create API calls





                            